# Replace your existing intelligence-related .gitignore lines with these:

intelligence/raw_data/
intelligence/output/events/
intelligence/output/parse_failures.json
intelligence/output/manifest.json

# NOTE: intelligence/output/context/venue_stats.json,
# intelligence/output/context/player_stats.json, and
# intelligence/output/context/player_aliases.json are INTENTIONALLY
# NOT ignored - these three small files (under 4MB total) are what
# app.py loads at runtime via the Insight Engine, and Render only
# deploys what's committed to git. Everything else in output/ (the
# 22,000+ per-match event files, the full manifest, raw Cricsheet data)
# stays local-only - regenerate locally when you want fresh data, then
# re-commit just these three context files.
